Describe a person who encouraged you and helped you achieve a goal
- who this person is
- what goal it was
- what they did to help you
- explain how you felt about them

I’d like to talk about my best friend, An, who played a crucial role in helping me achieve my goal of learning how to swim. She is a real swimming enthusiast and has been practicing the sport for many years, so she has a lot of experience.

I first set this goal when I was a first-year university student, as I wanted to find a healthy way to stay in shape. When I mentioned this to her, she immediately suggested swimming and even offered to teach me herself, which gave me the confidence to give it a try.

To be honest, I found it quite challenging at the beginning. I struggled to stay afloat, got tired very quickly, and sometimes even swallowed water, which made me feel discouraged. There were moments when I seriously considered giving up.

However, An was incredibly patient and supportive throughout the process. She guided me step by step, corrected my technique, and constantly motivated me with encouraging words whenever I felt frustrated. Thanks to her dedication and encouragement, I gradually improved and was able to swim confidently after about three months.

Since then, swimming has become one of my favorite activities, and we often go to the pool together on weekends. I feel extremely grateful to her, not only for helping me achieve this goal but also for teaching me the importance of persistence. Without her support, I don’t think I would have made it.
